## Methodology

### 1. Hate‚ÄëSpeech Dataset & Pre‚Äëprocessing

We sampled **100 Ukraine ‚Äúbiolab‚Äù hate‚Äëspeech posts** (tweets, forum messages, etc.) from a larger misinformation corpus. All content was English‚Äëlanguage and geopolitically themed to minimize topical variance. After stripping user identifiers, we only applied basic text‚Äëcleaning‚Äîour language model (LM) natively handles informal spelling and emojis.

### 2. Counter‚ÄëSpeech Generation Pipeline

Our two‚Äëstage pipeline combines **Retrieval‚ÄëAugmented Generation (RAG)** with **BEND‚Äëstyle prompting**.

1. **Evidence retrieval.** Each post is embedded (mxbai‚Äëembed, 1024‚Äëd) and queried against a domain‚Äëspecific vector database containing government archives, RAND reports, and other vetted sources. We re‚Äërank the top candidates via **Maximal Marginal Relevance (MMR)** to maximize relevance and diversity, then pass the selected passages to the LM as context.
2. **Response generation.** A 70‚ÄëB‚Äëparameter **LLaMA‚Äë70B‚ÄëInstruct** model receives the hate post, retrieved evidence, and a prompt template specifying one of six **BEND persuasion personas**‚Äî*Excite, Enhance, Distort, Dismay, Explain,* or *Engage.* Chain‚Äëof‚Äëthought instructions guide the model to ground its argument in the evidence and follow the requested persuasive style.

### 3. Evaluation

#### 3.1 LLM‚ÄëBased Persuasiveness Scoring

The same LLaMA‚Äë70B model is repurposed as a **‚Äújudge LLM.‚Äù** Prompted to act as three independent reviewers, it rates each counter on **five criteria**: (1) *Trustworthiness,* (2) *Attitude‚ÄëChange Potential,* (3) *Clarity & Depth,* (4) *Knowledge‚ÄëGap Fulfilment,* and (5) *BEND‚ÄëSpecific Effectiveness.* Scores range 1‚Äë5 with short justifications. We average the three virtual judges‚Äô ratings for analysis.

#### 3.2 Human Crowd‚ÄëSourced Evaluation

To validate automated scores, we run a small Amazon Mechanical Turk study (IRB details pending). Fluent English adults (N=\*) independently rate a randomly selected subset of counters using the same five‚Äëfactor, 5‚Äëpoint Likert scale; each item is evaluated by 3 workers for reliability. Exact sample size and compensation will be finalized (placeholders marked).

All model outputs and evidence passages are stored for reproducibility.






